HEADWORD: Secretness
<hw>Se"cret*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or
quality of being secret, hid, or concealed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Secretiveness; concealment.</def>
